{
  "name": "Conspirator's Crest",
  "type": "equipment",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This magic woven crest is adorned with raven feathers and carved jet.</p><p>While on your person, you have advantage on Charisma (Deception) checks. In addition, the crest has 5 charges and regains 1d4 + 1 expended charges daily at dusk. While wearing the crest, you can use a bonus action to expend 1 of its charges to disappear, releasing up to your proficiency modifier ravens from your location under your control that scatter into the air. Each raven has AC 12, 1 hit point, and can fly up to 50 feet as part of this bonus action without provoking opportunity attacks. At the start of your next turn, the ravens vanish, and you reappear in the space of one of the ravens (your choice). If all the ravens are reduced to 0 hit points, you reappear early in the same space as the last one that died. When you do, any excess damage dealt to the raven carries over to your normal form.</p><p><strong>Recharge:</strong> The Conspirator's Crest regains 1d4 + 1 expended charge at Dusk.</p>",
